{"word":"ἐσθής","slug":"ἐσθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐσθής</b></el> <el>(ἐσθής, ῆτος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕννυμι'><el>ἕννυμι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>dress, clothing, raiment</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, of <i>the clothes of several</i> persons, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>collectively, <i>clothes</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}